72
00:06:15,260 --> 00:06:18,300
死者名叫奥斯卡・华莱士 三十九岁
His name's Oscar Wallace... age 39,

73
00:06:18,370 --> 00:06:21,240
历史学教授 航海发烧友 儿童棒球教练
history professor, avid sailor, kids' baseball coach.

74
00:06:21,300 --> 00:06:23,500
他妻子三周前去了非洲
His wife's been in Africa for three weeks.

75
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:26,010
- 她本该今天早上回来的 - 去旅行还是别的
- She's due back this morning. - Safari or something?

76
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,870
不是 她是位人权律师 
No, she's a human rights lawyer.

77
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:29,770
艾思梅・贝尔克 你听说过她吗
Esme Belk. Have you heard of her?

78
00:06:29,770 --> 00:06:32,180
根据邻居们的说法
I guess she's famous or something,

79
00:06:32,180 --> 00:06:34,050
我猜她应该很有名气
according to the neighbours.

80
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:37,020
脖子周围有勒痕
Circumferential laceration on his neck.

81
00:06:37,090 --> 00:06:39,890
貌似是用绳索勒死的
It looks like ligature strangulation.

82
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:43,320
九岁大的孩子早上起来 想要的只是个华夫饼
Nine years old and you wake up, all you want is a waffle.

83
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:49,860
这么说 你和雷德利又开始搭档了
So, uh, you and Ridley are partners again?

84
00:06:49,930 --> 00:06:52,430
没有 我只是需要她的头脑
No, I just need her brain on this.

85
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,200
嗨
Hi.

86
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:05,340
真是惨绝人寰
The brutality is striking.

87
00:07:05,410 --> 00:07:07,580
没错 肩膀上有擦伤
Yeah, bruising on the shoulder.

88
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:09,550
肯定是踩住了胳膊
Must have just stepped on the arm

89
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:12,620
还抓住了手腕
and grabbed the wrist.

90
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:15,320
紧接着是难以忍受的疼痛 
Unbearable pain ensued...

91
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:17,160
除非他的胳膊是死后被扭断的
unless he snapped the arms post mortem,

92
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,410
但我认为是死前被扭断的
but I'm thinking ante mortem.

93
00:07:18,410 --> 00:07:20,120
- 为什么 - 你看 这么好的房子
- Why? - Well, it's a nice house,

94
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:23,930
他应该很有钱 行凶者也许想要图财
he's got money; Killer probably wanted some of it.

95
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,230
如果真的是想敲诈
There's easier parts of the body to break

96
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:28,770
还有更容易下手的身体部位
if extortion's the name of the game.

97
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:31,800
"给我钱 不然我就卸了你的胳膊"
"Give me the money or I'll break your arms."

98
00:07:31,870 --> 00:07:33,840
先一边 然后另一边
First one, then the other.

99
00:07:33,910 --> 00:07:36,410
然后他的头使劲上下挣扎 于是行凶者
Then his head's bobbing up and down, so the killer slips

100
00:07:36,470 --> 00:07:38,870
找了根绳子勒住他的脖子 然后
a ligature around his neck, and then

101
00:07:38,940 --> 00:07:40,880
就只剩下了无边的黑暗
it's nothing but darkness.

102
00:07:40,950 --> 00:07:42,880
胳膊肯定是在传达一个信息
The arms, they gotta be a message,

103
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:46,250
是在暗示什么 一个标志 它们想表达什么呢
an allusion to something, a sign. What do they signify?

104
00:07:50,390 --> 00:07:53,120
艾登 加利格拉说是你让我来这儿的
Aidan, Caligra said that you wanted me here with you,

105
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:55,690
但是我不
but I don't...

106
00:07:57,630 --> 00:08:00,230
我们在这儿做什么呢 艾登
What are we doing here, Aidan?

107
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:02,600
死尸一具 怪异的双臂
Dead guy, weird arms?

108
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:04,870
我以为你集中注意了
I thought you were paying attention.

109
00:08:24,090 --> 00:08:26,590
这是我家
This is my house.

110
00:08:28,590 --> 00:08:31,320
- 艾思梅・贝尔克・华莱士吗 - 是我 发生什么了
- Esme Belk Wallace? - Yes. What's going on?

111
00:08:31,390 --> 00:08:34,630
我女儿呢 奥斯卡呢
Where's my daughter? Where's Oscar?

112
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:47,340
- 嘿 - 嘿
- Hey. - Hey.

113
00:08:47,410 --> 00:08:49,880
- 她怎么样 - 你是她叔叔吗
- How is she? - You're her uncle?

114
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:52,210
- 是的 艾略特・贝尔克 - 里奥・贝克特
- Yeah, Elliott Belk. - Leo Beckett.

115
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:55,650
我们通过电话 呃 奥利维亚还没缓过来
We spoke on the phone. Um... Olivia's still in shock.

116
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,650
在某种程度上她能作出回应 
She's responsive to a degree,

117
00:08:57,650 --> 00:08:58,770
但是她还是不愿开口说话
but she's not talking yet,

118
00:08:58,770 --> 00:09:01,120
我们还在等你姐姐的电话
and we're still waiting for your sister to call.

119
00:09:01,190 --> 00:09:03,250
她的邻居说她出差了
Her neighbour said that she's away on business?

120
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,320
呃 没错 她本该今天早上回来的
Uh, yeah, she's supposed to be back this morning.

121
00:09:05,390 --> 00:09:07,290
- 我能进去吗 - 可以
- Can I? - Yeah.

122
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:08,890
谢谢
Thanks.

123
00:09:16,570 --> 00:09:19,270
嘿 宝贝儿 嗨
Hey, sweetheart. Hi.

124
00:09:19,340 --> 00:09:21,970
嘿 我是艾略特叔叔
Hey, it's Uncle Elliott.

125
00:09:24,210 --> 00:09:25,740
你怎么样了
How you doing?

126
00:09:27,980 --> 00:09:32,480
我希望 一些熟人和安慰 或许会让她快点好过来
I'm hoping, with some familiarity and some comfort, that she'll come around soon.

127
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:38,820
嘿 不会有事的
Hey, it's gonna be OK.

128
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:43,260
我们有什么线索
So, what do we got?

129
00:09:43,330 --> 00:09:45,290
死者的妻子 那个人权律师
Victim's wife, the human rights lawyer.

130
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,400
- 没错 艾思梅 - 我们拿到了她的旅行记录
- Yeah, Esme. - We got her travel records.

131
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:48,890
她在刚果待了三周 对吧
She's been in the Congo for three weeks, right?

132
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,370
你说她的航班是今早八点到的
You said her flight arrived at 8am this morning?

133
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:56,670
- 没错 - 事实并非如此 她的航班是昨天早上八点的
- Yup. - It didn't. Her flight got in at 8am  yesterday morning.

134
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:58,640
我一个小时前才看见她
I just watched her climb out

135
00:09:58,710 --> 00:10:00,980
从机场豪华轿车上下来 带着行李之类的
of an airport limo an hour ago, luggage and everything.

136
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:03,470
这么说 除非艾思梅・贝尔克的记录出错了 
Well, either Esme Belk's records are wrong,

137
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:04,410
不然她肯定在撒谎
or she likes to dabble in deception.

138
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:07,320
那么过去的二十四小时她在哪儿
Well, where's she's been for the last 24 hours?

139
00:10:07,380 --> 00:10:10,650
- 你去哪儿 - 带她过来
- Where you headed? - To bring her in.

140
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:13,650
你去吗
Are you going?

141
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:16,160
搞什么名堂 你们一起工作可你不去
What's the deal? You guys are working together but you're not?

142
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:19,490
不晓得
I don't know.

143
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:22,700
他们一起离开了黑文谷
And together they left Valley Haven.

144
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:25,230
开始了森林之行
They journeyed deep into the woods

145
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:29,000
穿过冰冷的丛林雪堆
through icy trees and snow drifts,

146
00:10:29,070 --> 00:10:31,800
经过日日夜夜
through day and night,

147
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:35,710
