206
00:13:26,570 --> 00:13:28,670
她没有那么大的力气 弄折自己丈夫的手臂
She's not strong enough to break her husband's arms.

207
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:31,710
但是她的经济条件足以雇人作案
But she's rich enough to pay someone to do it for her.

208
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:48,560
你这是在干什么
What are you doing?!

209
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:03,040
不要 不要
No, no, no.

210
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,580
不要 不要
No! No!

211
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,480
不要 不要
No! No!

212
00:14:22,690 --> 00:14:24,620
第一位嫌疑人
Door number one:

213
00:14:24,690 --> 00:14:27,150
坦艾民 缅甸国籍
Aye Min Than. Burmese national.

214
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:30,160
去年往她家客厅窗户里扔了一枚手榴弹
Threw a grenade through her living room window last year.

215
00:14:30,230 --> 00:14:32,090
虽然不是真手榴弹 但还是扔了
Wasn't real, but still.

216
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:34,100
第二位嫌疑人 戈伦・米洛维奇
Door number Two: Goran Milovic.

217
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,300
塞尔维亚人 几年前在住宅外被捕
A Serbian. He was arrested outside the house

218
00:14:36,370 --> 00:14:39,330
当时艾思梅正为一位克罗地亚叛军领袖辩护
a few years ago when Esme was defending a Croat rebel leader.

219
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,970
他在他们家前院纵火烧树
He set fire to a tree in their front yard.

220
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:45,240
- 她手头上的案子呢 - 那是第三个嫌疑人:
- What about her current case? - Door number three:

221
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:47,240
艾尼沃克・阿德伊米 加拿大落地移民
Enioke Adeyemi. He's a landed immigrant,

222
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:49,510
祖籍刚果民主共和国
originally from the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

223
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:52,450
他的母亲和姐姐都是前儿童军的受害者
His mother and sister were victims of the former child soldier.

224
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:54,650
艾思梅的辩护方 法西纳・戈翁
Esme's defending, Fasina Gowon.

225
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,750
这家伙在八岁时
The guy was enslaved to the Lord's Resistance

226
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:58,820
沦为圣主抵抗军的奴隶 期间被洗脑
Army when he was eight, and brainwashed.

227
00:14:58,890 --> 00:15:02,890
阿德伊米先生几周前在咖啡厅遇到艾思梅 便对她大吼大叫
Mr. Adeyemi confronted Esme at a café a few weeks ago, started yelling;

228
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:05,020
当时他携带了把小折刀 但是没有使用
He had a pocket knife on him, but he didn't use it.

229
00:15:05,090 --> 00:15:08,190
这些还只是没入狱 也没被驱逐出境的嫌疑人
And these are just the suspects that aren't in jail or deported already.

230
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:12,030
为什么还没带艾思梅・贝尔克去看她的女儿
Why has Esme Belk not been taken to see her daughter?

231
00:15:12,100 --> 00:15:14,530
因为她在撒谎 所以我给她时间
Because she's lying, so I'm stalling to give her time

232
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:18,810
在里面细想一下监禁的滋味
to ponder what incarceration is gonna look like from the inside.

233
00:15:18,820 --> 00:15:20,670
除非我们控告她 否则我们就得放人
We can't keep her any longer unless we charge her.

234
00:15:20,740 --> 00:15:22,740
你可以让她在去医院的路上好好想想
You can let her ponder on the way to the hospital.

235
00:15:41,460 --> 00:15:42,990
奥利维亚
Olivia?

236
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,660
宝贝儿
Sweetheart?

237
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:54,170
- 妈妈 - 哦
- Mom. - Oh!

238
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:03,750
我被尖叫声惊醒
I woke up 'cause there was screaming,

239
00:16:03,810 --> 00:16:06,080
我手足无措
and I didn't know what to do,

240
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:08,820
于是就躲进了被窝里
so I hid under the covers,

241
00:16:08,890 --> 00:16:15,320
当我下楼到大厅时 我听到有人像是在跑
and when I walked down the hall, I heard somebody, like, running,

242
00:16:15,390 --> 00:16:19,190
接着就听到了关门声...
and I heard the door shut...

243
00:16:19,260 --> 00:16:22,360
于是我了下楼
and then I went down the stairs,

244
00:16:22,430 --> 00:16:25,030
我看到...
and I saw...

245
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:26,900
没事了 没事了
It's OK, it's OK.

246
00:16:26,970 --> 00:16:28,700
没事了 宝贝
It's OK, sweetheart.

247
00:16:28,770 --> 00:16:31,070
我太对不起你了
I'm so sorry.

248
00:16:31,140 --> 00:16:33,540
我应该陪在你身边
I should have been there.

249
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:43,100
奥利维亚 你昨晚没有参加你朋友家的彻夜狂欢吗 
Olivia... didn't you go to a sleepover last night?

250
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:45,010
你爸爸上周给我发短信
Your Daddy texted me

251
00:16:45,010 --> 00:16:47,430
说你受邀参加一个彻夜狂欢派对 你没有去吗
last week that you got invited to a sleepover. You didn't go?

252
00:16:47,430 --> 00:16:50,860
我去了 后来我有点害怕 
I went, except I got scared later,

253
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:53,370
所以劳伦的爸爸就送我回家了
so Lauren's dad drove me home.

254
00:16:53,370 --> 00:16:56,360
奥利维亚 你到家时 你爸爸在哪里
Olivia, when you got home, where was your dad?

255
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:57,680
看电视
Watching TV.

256
00:16:57,680 --> 00:17:00,530
他把我抱进卧室 还说 "爱你 丽维亚小乖乖"
He tucked me in and said, "Love you, Livia-bug."

257
00:17:02,530 --> 00:17:05,350
没事了 小南瓜 不要说了
It's OK, Pumpkin. Shh, shh.

258
00:17:05,350 --> 00:17:07,460
没事了 没事了
It's OK, it's OK.

259
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:10,010
这么看来 凶手听到奥利维亚下床 
So, the killer heard Olivia get out of bed.

260
00:17:10,010 --> 00:17:11,310
让他很吃惊 随即逃走
It surprised him, and he ran.

261
00:17:11,310 --> 00:17:13,900
- 他原本以为有更多时间 - 更神不知鬼不觉
- He thought he had more time. - And more privacy.

262
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:15,580
有可能他本不知道奥利维亚在家 
Could be he didn't know Olivia was there,

263
00:17:15,580 --> 00:17:16,590
或者根本不知道奥斯卡有个孩子
or even that Oscar had a kid.

264
00:17:16,590 --> 00:17:20,750
抑或是他清楚奥利维亚的安排 知道她不会在家
Or he knew Olivia's schedule and knew she wasn't gonna be at home.

265
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:22,710
她听到尖叫后被惊醒
And she woke up because she heard him screaming,

266
00:17:22,710 --> 00:17:24,760
这么说他的手臂是在死前被折断的
so his arms were broken before he died.

267
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:27,580
没错 你要留下来吗
Yup. You sticking around?

268
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:28,800
恩 再待会儿 
Yeah, for a bit.

269
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,710
我想看看奥利维亚还能不能回忆起什么来
I'm gonna see if Olivia can remember anything else.

270
00:17:30,710 --> 00:17:31,920
- 好吧 - 艾登 等等
- OK. - Aidan, wait.

271
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:36,030
我不想再这样在你身边工作 而不和你搭档
I don't want to go on working near you and not with you,

272
00:17:36,030 --> 00:17:37,660
所以要是我们再也不能搭档了 
so if we can't ever be partners again,

273
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:39,940
你可以现在就告诉我吗
can you just let me know now?

274
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:54,580
打扰一下
Excuse me.

275
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:57,580
噢 你好
Oh, hi.

276
00:17:57,580 --> 00:17:59,580
对不起 我是丹妮拉・雷德利
Sorry. I'm Daniella Ridley,

277
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:02,510
和警察共事的精神科医生 你是和华莱士家一起的吗
a psychiatrist with the police. Are you with the Wallace family?

278
00:18:02,510 --> 00:18:05,250
对 对 我叫艾略特・贝尔克.
Uh, yeah, yeah, I'm Elliott Belk.

279
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,580
- 你好 - 你好 是艾思梅的哥哥
- Hi. - Hi. Uh, Esme's brother,

280
00:18:07,650 --> 00:18:09,280
奥利维亚的舅舅
uh, Olivia's uncle.

281
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:13,990
- 里面都还好吧 - 嗯
- Everything all right in there? - Well, uh,

282
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:17,830
奥利维亚睡着了 艾思梅在里面陪她 所以...
Olivia's finally asleep, and Esme's in there with her, so...

283
00:18:17,890 --> 00:18:19,830
好吧 那正好趁现在 我可以问你一些
OK, well, maybe now would be a good time if I could ask you

284
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:21,830
关于你妹妹和她家人的问题吗
some questions about your sister and her family?

285
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:25,630
好 当然
Uh, yeah, yeah, sure.

286
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:28,140
你和奥斯卡亲近吗
Were you and Oscar close?

287
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:31,570
我可能和奥利维亚最亲近
Well, uh, I was probably closest with Olivia.

288
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:34,160
艾思梅经常出差 
You know, Esme goes out of town all the time,

289
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,910
奥斯卡晚上又要上课
and Oscar teaches his night classes,

290
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:38,380
就经常由我来照看奥利维亚
so I end up babysitting for Olivia a fair bit.

291
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:40,410
她有你陪着真是幸运
Oh. She's lucky to have you.

292
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:42,580
是吗 我倒不知道
Ah, yeah, I don't know about that.

293
00:18:42,650 --> 00:18:45,390
我们有一个只有我俩才懂的笑话
Um, we have this little inside joke

294
00:18:45,450 --> 00:18:47,520
